profile.profileDescription: Use this profile if you want a system that is compliant with baseline CDWA-Lite 1.1

label.name: Alternate identifiers
label.description: Any additional unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.

label.name: Description/Descriptive Note
label.description: A relatively brief essay-like text that describes the content and context of the work

label.name: Caption
label.description: Short descriptive caption for item.

label.name: Georeference
label.description: Coordinates documenting the location of the item

label.name: Library of Congress Subject Headings
label.description: Library of Congress Subject headings describing this object. To add a new heading simply type the first few letters of the heading and choose the desired one from the displayed list of possible matches.

label.name: Notes (internal use only)
label.description: Notes regarding item

label.name: GeoNames
label.description: A Geographic lookup that takes search text, passes it to the GeoNames search service and provides a dropdown with search results (ordered by score). Selected geoname is stored as both text (name, country, continent and ID) and the service URL identifier.

label.name: Work type
label.description: A term or terms identifying the specific kind of object or work being described. For a collection, include repeatable instances for terms identifying all of or the most important items in the collection.

label.name: Source title
label.description: The source for the title, generally a published source.

label.name: Source of name creator
label.description: The source for the name, generally a published source.

label.name: Nationality
label.description: National or cultural affiliation of the person or corporate body.

label.name: Vital dates
label.description: A description of the lifespan of the person or the existence of the corporate body, using ca. and any other expressions of uncertainty or nuance. For Birth and Death date attributes, record years of birth and death, estimated where necessary. For a corporate body, use birthdate and deathdate to record the dates of founding and dissolution.

label.name: Gender
label.description: The sex of the individual. Not applicable for corporate bodies.

label.name: Role
label.description: The role played by the creator or other agent in the creation or production of the work.

label.name: Attribution qualifier
label.description: A qualifier used when the attribution is uncertain, is in dispute, when there is more than one creator, when there is a former attribution, or when the attribution otherwise requires explanation.

label.name: Extent
label.description: When there are multiple creators, a term indicating the part of the work created by this creator.

label.name: Display measurements
label.description: Information about the dimensions, size, or scale of the work, presented in a syntax suitable for display to the end-user and including any necessary indications of uncertainty, ambiguity, and nuance. It may include the scale of the work. It may also include the number of the parts of a complex work, series, or collection.

label.name: Indexing measurement set
label.description: The dimensions, size, shape, scale, format, or storage configuration of the work, including volume, weight, area or running time. Measurements are formatted to allow retrieval; preferably in metric units where applicable; if multiple parts of the work are measured, repeat the Indexing Measurements Set element.

label.name: Display materials/techniques
label.description: An indication of the substances or materials used in the creation of a work, as well as any implements, production or manufacturing techniques, processes, or methods incorporated in its fabrication, presented in a syntax suitable for display to the end-user and including any necessary indications of uncertainty, ambiguity, and nuance.

label.name: Indexing materials/techniques set
label.description: Materials and techniques indexed with controlled terms for retrieval; if multiple parts of the work require separate materials and techniques, or if you are recording media and support separately, repeat this element with the type attribute and/or the extent sub-element.

label.name: Display state
label.description: A description of the state of the work; used primarily for prints and other multiples.

label.name: Display edition
label.description: A description of the edition of the work; used primarily for prints and other multiples.

label.name: Source display state/edition
label.description: The published source of the state or edition information.

label.name: Style
label.description: Term that identifies the named, defined style, historical or artistic period, movement, group, or school whose characteristics are represented in the work being catalogued.

label.name: Culture
label.description: Name of the culture, people, or nationality from which the work originated.

label.name: Display creation date
label.description: A concise description of the date or range of dates associated with the creation, design, production, presentation, performance, construction, or alteration of the work or its components, presented in a syntax suitable for display to the end-user and including any necessary indications of uncertainty, ambiguity, and nuance.

label.name: Indexing dates set
label.description: Materials and techniques indexed with controlled terms for retrieval; if multiple parts of the work require separate materials and techniques, or if you are recording media and support separately, repeat this element with the type attribute and/or the extent sub-element.

label.name: Location/Repository Set
label.description: The name and geographic location of the repository that is currently responsible for the work, or, for monumental works and architecture, the geographic location of the work.

label.name: Inscriptions
label.description: A description or transcription of any distinguishing or identifying physical lettering, annotations, texts, markings, or labels that are affixed, applied, stamped, written, inscribed, or attached to the work, excluding any mark or text inherent in the materials of which the work is made (record watermarks in Display Materials/Techniques).

label.name: Rights for Work
label.description: Information about rights management; may include copyright and other intellectual property statements required for use regarding the work. If the holder of the reproduction rights to the image/resource differs from the rights for the work, use rightsResource.

label.name: Link Resource
label.description: A uri/url reference that is universal and in the worldwide web environment.

label.name: Resource Type
label.description: The generic identification of the medium of the image or other resource.

label.name: Rights for Resource
label.description: Information about rights regarding the image or other resource. Use this sub-element if the holder of the reproduction rights for the image/resource differs from the holder of rights for the work. See also Rights Work above.

label.name: Resource View Description
label.description: A description of the spatial, chronological, or contextual aspects of the work as captured in the view of this particular image or other resource.

label.name: Resource View Type
label.description: The specific vantage point or perspective of the view.

label.name: Resource View Subject Term
label.description: Terms or phrases that characterize the subject matter of the work as it is depicted in a specific image or other resource.

label.name: Resource View Date
label.description: A date or range of dates associated with the creation or production of the image. This is not necessarily the same as the date of production of the resource (e.g., a print of a negative may be made years after the image was first captured on film). For the date of the resource, use Resource Date.

label.name: Resource Source
label.description: Identification of the agency, individual, repository, or publication from which the image or other resource was obtained, including a bibliographic citation in the case of copy photography.
